5:
Ammo, check. Equipment,
checkerino. Flashbangs... 'nades...
Now where'd I put them?
14:
That's the one, thanks! Looks like
they're expired though.
17:
You ever think about tidying up
some of this clutter?
21:
I'd hate to throw any of this stuff
away—too many memories, ya
know?
Anyway, that should do it, I think!
26:
Remember the plan—infiltrate the
premises and find that World
Flipper. You guys ready?
29: We are, but... are you okay with this?
33:
We appreciate the help, but
perhaps Love was right. If something
were to go wrong—
37:
Don't worry about me. I just want to
see the sky... more than anything.
47:
Is this the part where I'm supposed
to blush and get all teary-eyed?
58:
Yeah? Well... take a screenshot,
maybe it'll last longer.
63:
Is seeing the sky really worth taking
on an entire corporate empire?
66:
Yeah, it might sound pretty silly to
YOU, but to me... well, it's like a
faraway dream.
70:
When we look up, we don't see the
real sky. Just corporate logos and
flashy advertisements.
73:
It IS quite a view to take in. Not a
single star to be seen.
76:
A fake sky covered in propaganda
to blind the masses.
78:
The corporations that run this world
have already decided what our lives
are—and where their products fit in
them.
81:
But once you've loaded the spirit of
freedom into the chambers of your
heart... nobody can take that from
you.
85:
I just want her to be able to look up
to the night sky one day and see it
for real—not a neon skyline filled
with advertisements, you know?
88: Is that too much to ask, you think?
96: You really care for Love, don't you?
99: She's the best partner I could ask for.
102:
*sigh* It sucks that I couldn't do this
run with her though.
107:
It's for you, Bulleta. A message from
Love.
111:
Geez, that idiot... She should've just
joined us in the first place.
116:
Look sharp, everyone! We're going in
tonight!
119:
Love's provided us with maps of the
entire DAN facility. In 3D too!
122:
Wow, you weren't kidding about her
being a prodigy!
126:
It appears to be an underground
tunnel of sorts. And it looks like
there's... something beyond?
130:
As long as we can get down there
somehow, that should be our ticket
in. Easy enough.
132:
Time to grab destiny by the horns
and show those nerds what it REALLY
means to be free!
138:
All clear! Just as expected, the
security's sparse around these parts.
141:
We're going underground from here,
right? Looks like it might take a
while...
144:
I assume we'll try to lay low in the
meantime, right?
147:
Heck no! It's always better to face
your problems head-on, am I right?
153:
Hack and destroy, baby!
Whoever wants to get blasted in the
face, step right up!
